						               													<description>Hello Kitty and her friends have a nice day ahead and must decide what to do. But every one has his preferences (randomly distributed in the beginning of the game). Where they go?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are 16 different activities and the player use a dice to manipulate the position of every activity in a &amp;quot;Preference Scale&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each time an activity reach the spot 8 in the preference scale, the players stop the game to make a decision: Are we according to go to this activity? In order to do so, every player has a hand of five cards (4 &amp;quot;No&amp;quot; cards and 1 &amp;quot;Yes&amp;quot; card). If any player use a No Card, the activity is discarded. Yes Cards return to the players, but &amp;quot;No&amp;quot; cards are also discarded, so the players will have less opportunities to use &amp;quot;No&amp;quot; cards during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If an activity receives only yes cards, the game ends and the players receive victory points according the position of his/her preference activity in the preference scale. Discarded activities bring no victory points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
